        "id": 258609,
        "name": "Talya (she/her)",
        "username": "rassilon1963",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/rassilon1963/{size}/31625_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-01-10T13:15:55.709Z",
        "cooked": "<p>while not exactly the same question, this is very similar to this thread:</p><aside class=\"quote\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"64326\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/j/c0e974/48.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/why-not-share-your-username-online/64326\">Why not share your username online?</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/general/7\"><span data-category-id=\"7\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #AC41A9; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category \" title=\"Anything related to Signal which does not fit into the Support, Feature Requests or Development categories.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">General Discussion</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    For a small bookshop we use  signal to chat internally between workers. We have signal-desktop on our shop computer. Today I created a signal username. Now I was wondering why I would not share the qr-code of our username on our website so customers can contact us using signal. \nSince Signal is saying “share only with people you trust” I am wondering why we would not want to do this. Sure maybe we get some spam, but that is not that different then from email?\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>\nand i’ll just put here what i’ve put there because it’s essentially the same answer:</p><aside class=\"quote\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"64326\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/rassilon1963/48/31625_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/why-not-share-your-username-online/64326/5\">Why not share your username online?</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/general/7\"><span data-category-id=\"7\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #AC41A9; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category \" title=\"Anything related to Signal which does not fit into the Support, Feature Requests or Development categories.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">General Discussion</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    The main issue with sharing your username publicly is it’s yet another sign pointing to you. It’s like publishing an email or a phone number publicly online. \nIf you don’t worry about spammers, then you’re fine. But the main worry is that, spammers. Getting rid of them once they have your account, if they’re relentless, can be quite hard (see <a href=\"https://signal.miraheze.org/wiki/Privacy_tips\" class=\"inline-onebox\">Privacy tips - Signal Wiki</a>).\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
