        "created_at": "2025-01-10T14:23:35.967Z",
        "cooked": "<p>A common thread type here includes requests for features that limit various abilities of Signal contacts. The common response is that Signal is designed so that you don’t need to trust Signal, but you do need to trust your contacts. You can of course share your “username”, QR code, or link, with anyone you like. As <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/rassilon1963\">@rassilon1963</a> said above, it is similar to sharing your phone number or email address, except that it only matters within Signal.</p>",
